sections:
  0. the-single-bottle [36mcinematic[0m/xl  Open on the one bottle alone in frame — no clutter, no comparison — establishing that Refugio is singular by design: one bottle, one agave, one family.
  1. three-generations [36mnarrative[0m/lg  Introduce the family lineage — grandfather, father, current maestro mezcalero — as the source of the bottle's authority, not a marketing claim.
  2. the-agave        [36masymmetric[0m/lg  Isolate the single agave varietal (Espadín, hand-selected) as the one differentiator worth remembering — everything else in the process serves this one plant.
  3. the-palenque     [36mtimeline[0m/xl  Walk through the traditional production process — roasting in earthen pits, stone-mill crushing, wild fermentation, copper-still distillation — as ritual, not manufacturing steps.
  4. tasting-notes    [36meditorial[0m/md  Slow down further into sensory language — smoke, earth, citrus, mineral — giving the visitor a reason to imagine drinking it, not just admire it.
  5. the-maker's-word [36meditorial[0m/sm  A single quote from the current maestro mezcalero grounding the brand's calm confidence in one authentic human voice, isolated for weight.
  6. one-bottle-again [36mcinematic[0m/lg  Return to the bottle in full, now with reverence earned by the story — closing the loop and inviting acquisition without hard-selling.

